bilingual.source: The dermatologist advised him not to scratch the macula.

list.abstract: Scratch是由麻省理工学院的“终身幼儿园团队”设计开发的一款图形化编程工具，旨在让程序设计语言初学者不需要先学习语言语法便能设计产品，主要面对青少年开放，支持Mac、安卓、windows系统平台。 Scratch通过点击并拖拽的方式，完成编程，可以使儿童或者成人编程初学者学习编程基础概念等。
唱片《Scratch》（中译名：成长印迹），日本著名流行歌手木村kaela正式出道后的第3张专辑。2007年2月7日由哥伦比亚唱片公司出版发售。

yingyinNormal.zh: 好运不会乱抓，他保证了。

yingyinNormal.en: Should we just scratch that one and just move on?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我能不能划掉那个问题，然后继续？

yingyinNormal.en: Joey, it says Best Supporting Actress. I can scratch that right off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊，上面写着“最佳女配角奖”。我可以把那个刮掉。

yingyinNormal.en: Grandpa, there's a big hole in your boat. It's just a scratch. Grandpa's boat is sinking.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爷爷，你的船被撞了一个大洞。只是碰撞了一下而已。喔，爷爷你的船正在下沉呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Thank God you didn't try to fan out the magazines. I mean, she'll scratch your eyes right out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 幸好你没摊开杂志，否则她铁定会挖出你的眼睛。

yingyinNormal.en: They were looking for respectable types, preferably virgins. They liked to train them from scratch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们寻找佳丽，只要处女，想从零开始训练她们。

yingyinNormal.en: Thank you. No, I know what I would do. I would probably scratch his eyes out. That's what I would do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢。不，我知道自己会做什么，可能会把他的眼珠子都挖出来，我应该会这么干。

yingyinNormal.en: You say you recognize the scratch? I wish to confirm this belief before I tarnish his name any further.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说你认识绘制此图的笔法？我想先进一步确认，然后再说出此人的名字。

yingyinNormal.en: You think he was gonna let you off without a scratch? You'd still be standing there if I hadn't hit you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你以为他会让你毫发无损地离开？如果不是我把你割伤了，你现在还站在那里呢。

yingyinNormal.en: First there's a layer of ladyfingers, then a layer of jam, then custard, which I made from scratch, then raspberries, more ladyfingers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先是一层小松糕，然后是果酱，然后是我自己做的乳蛋糕，然后是覆盆子，然后又是小松糕。

yingyinNormal.en: Thanks. And, Sheldon, I know tonight's the night you eat Thai food, so I went to the Asian market, got all the ingredients and made it from scratch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢。谢尔顿，我知道今晚是你的泰国菜之夜，所以我去了亚洲超市，买了一切所需材料从零开始学。

yingyinNormal.en: You do know that my birthday's tomorrow, right? This is just step one of your birthday weekend. Now, would you care to join me for an authentic frontier dinner made entirely from scratch?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但你知道我生日是明天的吧？这只是你的生日周末第一阶段。你愿意坐下与我一同享用正宗拓荒者晚餐吗全部手工做的呢？

examination_example.sentence: As the CFO of Macy's put it recently, "We're frankly <highlight>scratching</highlight> our heads."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如梅西百货首席财务官最近所说，“坦率地说，我们正在挠头。”

examination_example.sentence: If you've ever started a sentence with, "If I were you... " or found yourself <highlight>scratching</highlight> your head at a colleague's agony over a decision.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你曾经用“如果我是你……”或者你发现自己在为同事做决定的痛苦而挠头。

examination_example.sentence: The models couldn't sit in them, and they even got <highlight>scratched</highlight> from the plastics under their arms.

examination_example.sentence: A girl riding a bike hit and <highlight>scratched</highlight>（刮）a parked expensive car by accident when she was busily looking at a road sign.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个女孩骑着自行车，在忙着看路标的时候，不小心撞到了一辆停在路边的名贵轿车，并被刮伤。

examination_example.sentence: He told her that she didn’t need to pay any money for the <highlight>scratched</highlight> part of the car.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他告诉她，她不需要为汽车的划痕部分支付任何钱。

examination_example.sentence: They even put their noses to the ground and <highlight>scratched</highlight> their heads.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们甚至把鼻子贴在地上，挠着头。

examination_example.sentence: The moment I arrived in Germany, I felt like I was starting from <highlight>scratch</highlight> (从头开始).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到达德国的那一刻，我感觉自己是从零开始的。
